===Notes===
{{notelist}}

==Rolling stock==
Services on the line are provided by six-car Type B trains, which have a total capacity of 1440. These trains are the same as those which run on Line 1.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.railjournal.com/index.php/asia/harbin-opens-metro-line-3.html |title=Harbin opens metro Line 3 |last=Barrow |first=Keith |date=26 January 2017 |publisher=International Railway Journal |access-date=3 February 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.camet.org.cn/index.php?m=content&c=index&a=show&catid=42&id=1562 |title=哈尔滨地铁3号线一期首列列车抵哈调试 |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=27 September 2016 |website=camet.org.cn |access-date=3 February 2018 |language=Chinese}}</ref>

==Future plans==
[[File:Harbin_Metro_System_Map_Line3_2018.png|center|800px]]
The {{convert|32|km|miles|abbr=on}} second phase of the line, which extends it to the southeast and northwest, began construction in 2017. It consists of 30 stations, of which 19 are on the southeastern portion and the remaining 11 on the northwestern. The southeastern portion would commence operations in 2020 while the northwestern would do so in 2022.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://newhouse.hrb.fang.com/2017-08-17/26075543_all.htm |title=哈尔滨地铁3号线增设4座车站 沿线哈慈新盘盘点 |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=17 August 2017 |website=newhouse.hrb.fang.com |language=Chinese|access-date=3 February 2018 }}</ref>

Eventually, the line is planned to run in a circle around Harbin and would be {{convert|37|km|miles|abbr=on}} long, with 34 stations.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://district.ce.cn/newarea/roll/201410/22/t20141022_3753092.shtml |title=哈尔滨地铁3号线34座站点公布 贯穿道里道外等四区 |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=22 October 2014 |website=district.ce.cn |access-date=3 February 2018 |language=Chinese }}</ref>

